# playhead.m8script — proves the playhead ROW actually advances during
# playback, not just that the transport flag is set (Tier 2,
# M8_APP_AUTOMATION_SPEC.md).
#
# Uses songs/sunrise.m8s (the startup song, real 16-bar content, no missing
# samples), loaded explicitly rather than relying on ambient boot state (see
# task6_test.m8script, which had to be fixed after silently drifting when the
# boot song changed). Two songs were tried and rejected first:
#   - V4EMPTY.m8s: zero note-on events across all 8 tracks (confirmed via
#     m8_render's note-on summary) -- nothing for the playhead to advance
#     through.
#   - TEST-FILE.m8s: triggers the missing-samples overlay on load, and
#     main.cpp's overlay-dismiss handler (`!missingSamplesMsg.empty() &&
#     event.type == SDL_EVENT_KEY_DOWN`) swallows the very next keydown --
#     including this script's `play` SPACE press -- to dismiss the overlay
#     instead of starting playback. Confirmed by reproducing directly: `play;
#     wait 60; assert_playing` never passes with TEST-FILE loaded.
#
# Previously this script only did `play; wait 120; assert_playing`, which
# (a) cannot prove the playhead row moved -- playhead indicators are drawn
# via drawLinePixel, outside the VRAM shadow grid `assert_screen` reads --
# and (b) raced the SPSC command-processing gap: across 12 runs, ASan builds
# passed 6/6 while Release passed 2/6 (status.md Known issues). wait_until
# re-checks the condition every single frame instead of guessing a frame
# count, and checkpoint_playhead/assert_playhead_advanced read the engine's
# own playhead atomic (Engine::getPlayheadState) directly.

load songs/sunrise.m8s
wait 1
assert_no_error

checkpoint_playhead
play
wait_until playhead_row >= 1
assert_playhead_advanced

stop
wait_until stopped
